descriptor.short_desc: AIRA Medium Pressure Stainless Steel Plug Valve – Ideal for industrial use, this valve supports air, water, oil, gas, nitrogen, and chemical media. Available with threaded or flanged ends, and lever or pneumatic actuator options.
descriptor.long_desc:
AIRA Medium Pressure Stainless Steel Plug Valve is a robust, corrosion-resistant valve designed for versatile industrial applications. Crafted from premium stainless steel, it ensures long-lasting performance even under challenging environments. It is suitable for controlling the flow of various media including air, water, oil, gas, nitrogen, and chemicals.

The valve is available in 2-way and 3-way configurations, with manual lever or pneumatic actuator operations, providing flexibility in automation and manual systems. With threaded or flanged end connections (150 Class), it is easy to integrate into existing pipelines.

This plug valve is particularly suitable for medium pressure systems, offering secure shutoff and reliable control across a wide range of industrial processes.

🔧 Specifications Overview:
Material: Stainless Steel

Pressure Rating: Medium Pressure

Media Handled: Air, Water, Oil, Gas, Nitrogen, Chemicals

Connection Type: Threaded End / Flanged End (150 Class)

Operation: Manual (Lever) / Pneumatic Actuated

Configuration: 2-Way and 3-Way

Brand: AIRA

descriptor.name: Channelier Building materials SS 304 Medium Pressure Stainless Steel Plug Valve, For Industrial, Size: 3/5" Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.code: Channelier Building materials SS 304 Medium Pressure Stainless Steel Plug Valve, For Industrial, Size: 3/5" Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.short_desc: Shyam Metals SS 304 Plug Valve (3/5"), designed for medium-pressure industrial applications. Corrosion-resistant stainless steel construction with a manual lever for reliable on-off flow control.
descriptor.long_desc:
The Shyam Metals SS 304 Medium Pressure Plug Valve, sized at 3/5", is a highly durable and efficient flow control device for industrial pipelines. Manufactured using premium-grade stainless steel (SS 304), this valve is engineered for medium pressure applications and offers excellent resistance to corrosion, high temperatures, and chemical exposure.

Its design features a rotating cylindrical or tapered plug, which aligns with or blocks the flow channel, allowing for quick shut-off or flow isolation. Operated manually using a lever mechanism, this plug valve ensures ease of operation and reliability under various operating conditions.

This valve is especially suited for industries like oil & gas, petrochemical, pharmaceutical, food processing, and water treatment, where chemical compatibility and long service life are critical. The sealing mechanism—whether elastomeric or metal-to-metal—ensures a tight shut-off with minimal leakage risk.

🔧 Specifications Overview:
Product Type: Plug Valve

Brand: Shyam Metals

Valve Size: 3/5"

Material: Stainless Steel (SS 304)

Pressure Rating: Medium Pressure

Usage/Application: Industrial

Operation: Manual Lever

End Connections: Typically Flanged or Threaded (as per availability)

Body Design: Cylindrical or tapered port plug valve

Flow Control: On-off isolation

🛠️ Key Features:
High resistance to corrosion and heat

Long-lasting SS 304 construction

Quick shut-off with simple lever operation

Ideal for controlling flow of gases, liquids, and chemicals

Available in a range of sizes and end connections

Suitable for high-demand industrial environments

descriptor.name: Channelier Building materials Stainless Steel Medium Pressure Pneumatic 2 Way Plug Valve, For Industrial Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.code: Channelier Building materials Stainless Steel Medium Pressure Pneumatic 2 Way Plug Valve, For Industrial Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.short_desc: AIRA 2-Way Stainless Steel Pneumatic Plug Valve** (16”), built for industrial medium-pressure systems. Designed per API 599, this non-lubricated, sleeved plug valve offers robust sealing, high flow efficiency, and is available with PTFE-based gaskets and plug sleeves.
descriptor.long_desc:
AIRA Stainless Steel Medium Pressure Pneumatic 2-Way Plug Valve in 16-inch size is a premium, industrial-grade valve engineered for precise flow control of air, water, oil, gas, and chemicals. Designed as per API 599 standards and suitable for ANSI Class 150 & 300, this plug valve is ideal for demanding applications across petrochemical, water treatment, and process industries.

The valve body and trim are available in multiple material grades such as ASTM A216 Gr. WCB, ASTM A351 Gr. CF8/CF8M/CF3M, Monel, Hastelloy, and Duplex, ensuring compatibility with aggressive media and extended service life. Its non-lubricated design with PTFE/CFT/GFT/RPTFE sleeved plug and gasket system provides tight shut-off, corrosion resistance, and reduced maintenance.

Equipped with pneumatic actuator, lever, or wrench operation, the valve ensures operational flexibility. Designed to handle temperatures up to 180°C, this valve offers low pressure drop, high efficiency, and superior sealing, making it a go-to solution for modern industrial systems.

🔧 Specifications Overview:
Product Name: Pneumatic 2-Way Plug Valve

Brand: AIRA

Valve Size: 16 inch

Material: Stainless Steel (various grades)

Material Grades Available:

ASTM A216 Gr. WCB

ASTM A351 Gr. CF8 / CF8M / CF3M

Monel, Hastelloy, Duplex

Media: Air, Water, Oil, Gas, Chemicals

Pressure: Medium Pressure

Temperature Range: Up to 180°C

Operator: Lever / Wrench / Pneumatic Actuator

Plug Sleeve Options: PTFE, CFT, GFT, RPTFE

Gasket Options: PTFE, CFT, GFT, RPTFE

Design Standard: API 599

End Connection: Screwed / Flanged (ANSI 150/300)

Warranty: 4 Years

Country of Origin: India

Production Capacity: 3000 Units

Delivery Time: 3–4 Days

Packaging: Polythene Bag / Corrugated Box

🛠️ Key Features:
Non-lubricated sleeved design for reduced maintenance

Designed to API 599 with ANSI 150/300 compatibility

Excellent chemical and thermal resistance

High flow capacity with low pressure drop

Long sealing life with PTFE-based gaskets and sleeves

Pneumatic operation for automated systems

descriptor.name: Channelier Building materials Wurth P80 Arizona Perfect Vehicle Dry Sandpaper Roll, Size: 115 mm X 25 M (w X L) Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.code: Channelier Building materials Wurth P80 Arizona Perfect Vehicle Dry Sandpaper Roll, Size: 115 mm X 25 M (w X L) Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.short_desc: Wurth P80 Arizona Perfect Sandpaper Roll (115 mm x 25 m) is a high-performance dry abrasive roll ideal for automotive refinishing. With D-paper backing and ceramic abrasive grain, it ensures superior material removal and a longer lifespan.
descriptor.long_desc:
The Wurth P80 Arizona Perfect Vehicle Dry Sandpaper Roll is engineered for automotive professionals seeking optimal sanding performance. Measuring 115 mm x 25 meters, this abrasive roll features a D-paper backing and P80 grit for effective material removal on a wide range of surfaces.

With ceramic abrasive grain (P40–P80 range), it offers up to 20% higher material removal rate and a service life improved by over 90%, making it highly efficient for heavy-duty surface preparation. It is particularly suited for sanding old paint, factory primers (KTL paints), plastic parts, fillers, and matting of topcoat paints.

Wurth’s advanced abrasive technology provides short sanding times and consistent results, contributing to faster job completion and reduced material waste. The product is also part of a broader abrasive system, available in grit sizes from P40 to P500, allowing for a complete sanding workflow from coarse removal to fine finishing.

🔧 Specifications Overview:
Brand: Wurth

Product Name: Arizona Perfect Vehicle Dry Sandpaper Roll

Grit Size: P80

Size: 115 mm (W) x 25 m (L)

Backing Material: D-paper

Packaging Type: Roll

Product Code: 5506247108961 1

Available Grit Sizes: P40, P60, P80, P100, P120, P150, P180, P220, P320

🛠️ Application Areas:
P40–P120:

Initial sanding of factory primers (KTL)

Removal of old paint and rust

Sanding damaged or dented areas to bare metal

Pre-sanding and edge levelling of fillers

P100–P500:

Matting of topcoats

Sanding of plain, acrylic, or clear lacquers

Preparation of water-based, synthetic, and 2K fillers and primers

descriptor.short_desc: Versatile Brown Corundum Sand Paper Roll (Grade 40–600), packed in a convenient box. Ideal for dry sanding across various surfaces, compatible with PSA and Hook & Loop systems.
descriptor.long_desc:
This Brown Corundum Sand Paper Roll offers high-performance dry sanding capability across a wide range of grades—from P40 to P600—making it suitable for everything from aggressive stock removal to fine surface finishing.

Packaged in a box for ease of storage and handling, the roll is made from premium dry abrasive paper, bonded with brown corundum (aluminum oxide) for excellent durability and cutting efficiency. It is highly adaptable and can be cut into custom-sized sheets for use with sheet sanders, board file sanders, or hand sanding blocks.

The roll supports both PSA (Pressure Sensitive Adhesive) and Kling-On® (Hook & Loop) systems, making it one of the most versatile and user-friendly abrasives for woodworkers, metal finishers, and automotive professionals alike.

descriptor.name: Channelier Building materials Elantas Electrical Insulation Varnishes, 500 ml Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.code: Channelier Building materials Elantas Electrical Insulation Varnishes, 500 ml Channelier Bulding & Construction Supplies
descriptor.short_desc: Elantas Electrical Insulation Varnish (500 ml) by Dr Beck is a high-performance phenolic insulation varnish, ideal for coating PCBs and SRBP components. With fast air drying, anti-tracking properties, and a thermal class rating of 130(B), it ensures reliable electrical insulation and protection.
descriptor.long_desc:
The Elantas Electrical Insulation Varnish (500 ml), from Dr Beck, is specially formulated for high-performance electrical insulation applications. Designed for coating PCB (Printed Circuit Boards) and SRBP (Self-Repairing Base Paper) components, this varnish ensures improved dielectric properties and mechanical bonding to enhance the longevity and performance of electrical systems.

The varnish is made from a phenolic chemical base, providing excellent thermal conductivity, resistance to moisture, and protection against chemically corrosive environments. It has a thermal class rating of 130(B) and can withstand temperatures up to 155°C, ensuring durability under harsh operating conditions. With a fast air drying formula and anti-tracking properties, this varnish is highly effective for impregnating and finishing insulation systems in electrical machines.

🔧 Specifications Overview:
Brand: Dr Beck

Product Name: Elantas Electrical Insulation Varnish

Packaging Size: 500 ml

Form: Liquid

Grade Standard: ELMO LUFT 1A - FD

Suggested Applications: Coating on PCBs, SRBP components

Chemical Base: Phenolic

Vapour Pressure: 0.32 kPa @ 20°C

Viscosity: 25-35 @ 23°C by DIN 53211/Cup4(s)

Breakdown Voltage (BDV): 7 BDV

Curing Cycle: RT/12 (Room Temperature/12 hours)

Temperature Resistance: 155°C

Thermal Class: 130(B)

Distinctive Properties: Fast Air Drying, Anti-tracking

Country of Origin: Made in India

🛠️ Key Features & Advantages:
Increased mechanical bonding to winding wires for better insulation

Improved dielectric properties for enhanced electrical performance

Improved thermal conductivity ensures efficient heat dissipation

Protection against moisture and chemically corrosive environments

Fast drying and anti-tracking for reliable insulation performance

Suitable for impregnation and finishing in electrical machines

descriptor.short_desc: Trident Zinc Chromate Primer (5L) is an oil-based anti-corrosive, anti-rust primer designed to protect surfaces from oxidation. Ideal for industrial and spray paint applications, it provides a gloss finish and enhances the durability of painted surfaces.
descriptor.long_desc:
Trident Zinc Chromate Primer (5L) is an oil-based, anti-corrosive primer designed to provide superior protection against rust and corrosion. This primer is specifically formulated with zinc chromate, which creates a protective layer on metal surfaces, preventing oxidation and enhancing the longevity of the underlying material.

Ideal for industrial use, spray paints, and applications in artists' paints and pigments, the Trident Zinc Chromate Primer can also be used in the manufacturing of linoleum. Due to its highly toxic nature, it is effective in destroying organic growth on surfaces, ensuring a clean and smooth finish. The product is packaged in a 5L can, providing excellent coverage for larger surfaces.

This primer is perfect for surfaces exposed to harsh environments, offering excellent adhesion and an attractive gloss finish that complements the top coat.

Product Name: Zinc Chromate Primer

Packaging Size: 5 liters

Primer Base Type: Oil-Based

Finish: Gloss

Form: Liquid

Packaging Type: Can

1. Handling and Transportation
Always handle goods with care to prevent scratches, dents, and breakage.

Use mechanical lifting aids for heavy items; avoid dragging goods across surfaces.

Protect edges and surfaces with padding during transport.

2. Storage
Store materials in a dry, well-ventilated area.

Keep items off the ground using pallets or blocks to prevent moisture absorption.

Protect from direct sunlight and rain with proper covers or tarps.

Do not stack excessively to avoid deformation or breakage.

3. Installation Preparation
Inspect all materials prior to installation; do not install damaged goods.

Ensure surfaces are clean, level, and prepared according to manufacturer’s specifications.

Acclimate materials like wood and laminate to the site environment before installation (usually 48–72 hours).

4. Cleaning and Maintenance
Clean regularly using appropriate, non-abrasive materials.

Avoid harsh chemicals unless specified safe for the material.

Wipe spills immediately to avoid staining or corrosion.

For outdoor items, rinse periodically to remove dust, pollutants, and bird droppings.

5. Environmental Protection
Apply protective coatings (e.g., sealants, primers, rust-proof layers) as recommended.

For wooden products, reapply finish/sealant every 1–2 years depending on exposure.

Ensure proper drainage to prevent water pooling on or around materials.

descriptor.short_desc: Salsa Macro Interior/Exterior Primer (20L) is a high-quality, water-based white primer designed for interior applications. Offering a matt finish, it provides excellent coverage and is ideal for preparing surfaces for painting. Perfect for both interior and exterior use.
descriptor.long_desc:
The Salsa Macro Interior/Exterior Primer (20L) is a water-based paint primer designed to ensure a smooth, durable surface for interior applications. With its matt finish and white color, it delivers a clean, professional look that enhances the adhesion of topcoats, ensuring long-lasting paint results.

This primer is perfect for preparing walls and surfaces for further painting, providing excellent coverage at 70 sqft per liter per coating. Packaged in a 20-liter bucket, it is ideal for large areas, offering cost-effective and reliable surface preparation.

With its superior adhesion properties, this primer also helps in achieving a consistent paint finish, reducing the need for additional coats. Suitable for both interior and exterior applications, it is an essential product for home improvement projects and industrial use.
